  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-8 clean, bounded envelope)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Operating envelope is explicitly bounded (flow rate 1–7 L/min, rotational speed 2000–4000 RPM, inlet pressure 5–20 mmHg, hematocrit 35–45%). All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors are assessed with achieved levels meeting or exceeding required levels. Decision: Accepted.",
