    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors have been assessed with achieved levels meeting or exceeding required levels. The operating envelope is explicitly bounded (flow rate 1–7 L/min, speed 2000–4000 RPM, hematocrit 35–45%, tip clearance ±0.05 mm) and all validation activities fall within these bounds. Monte Carlo UQ confirms the 95th-percentile NIH remains below the clinical threshold across the envelope. Sparse validation coverage (5 points) is acknowledged and captured in the UQ. The CFD model is accepted as credible for predicting absolute hemolysis levels for the Class III VAD device within the declared operating envelope.",
